				<div></div><div></div><div></div><div></div>Shadow Knight:<br><br>1. AC&nbsp; - The all important stat for plate tanks, espcially without warrior defensive<br>2. Shielding - increases tanking ability<br>3. Avoidance - increases tanking ability<br><br>4. Haste (have to have it) - increases tanking ability (more swings = more aggro)<br><br>5. Focii:<br>- magic focus for taps - increases tanking ability (stay alive longer)<br>- mana pres of somekind that covers detrimental spells - increases tanking ability (more mana for more taps and hate spells, utility spells for the group, etc in a burn situation)<br>- extended range - important for tagging, pulling and some other general things<br>- extended duration (eg chronoburn). - Makes snare (namely) last longer as well as the other dots for extra damage.<br>- I have a tertiary list as well, but if I don't have it, I don't have it (bazu/last blood augs have helped to make this easier to fulfil).<br><br>6. Mana regen (mine is maxed at 24 standing and I need it) - increases tanking ability (do not have to rest between mobs and I can cast all my spells without concern).<br><br>Everything else is gravy if it comes along with the gear that I got for the above reasons.<br><br>As far as SK itemization goes, one thing that we want the most is for non-visible gear not to conflict with drops from the most recent previous expansion, especially when one of those things is the SK quest/expansion item - mainly the Demiplane SK class item mask which lacks compared to Anguish masks from the expansion before, either by using a different non-visible slot for something that was particularly weak in the previous expansion, or by making the stats to where the class-only item is a no-brainer as an upgrade.<br><div></div><p>Message Edited by Xulan on <span class=date_text>07-06-2006</span> <span class=time_text>02:28 PM</span>
				
